         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Office of Lands &amp; Survey ¶ Melbourne, 12th. Augt. 1861. ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ By direction of the Honorable The President of the Board of Land and Works, I have the honor to acquaint you, for the information of...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.08.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Clement Hodgkinson</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">61/550, unit 8, p. 95, VPRS 7935/P1, outward letterbooks to the general public, VA 538 Department of Crown Lands and Survey, Public Record Office, Victoria.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Office of Lands &amp; Survey</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne, 12th. Augt. 1861.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By direction of the Honorable The President of the Board of Land and Works, I have the honor to acquaint you, for the information of the Committee of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Acclimatisation<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Society of Victoria, that the Society will be allowed the exclusive use of the Royal Park for depasturing purposes; and the question of leasing at a nominal rent a portion of the Park to the Society for the purpose of constructing thereon the various buildings, reservoirs, &amp;c, projected by the Society will be submitted for the consideration of the Board of Land and Works as soon as a definite plan of the portion of ground required (shewing its area and linear dimensions) is received at this Office.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>The Society had already held a competition for plans for laying out the intended enclosure of about 160 acres, awarding the prize of £50 to Mr Alfred Lynch, landscape gardener. An account of the intended buildings is given in the report announcing the award of the prize (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Geelong advertiser</seg>, 25 June 1861, p. 3).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The architects Purchas and Swyer calledfor tenders 'for about 1300 yards of FENCING required in Royal Park for the Acclimatization Society' (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Herald</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(Melbourne),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>8<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>October 1861, p.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>1).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Purchas<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>called for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>tenders for additional ground works (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 1 February 1862, p. 3). The <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Government estimates for 1862, tabled<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>17 January 1862, included £1000 for 'buildings, fences, and other works for Acclimatisation Society in the Royal Park' (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>20 January 1862, p. 5).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedt. Servant</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 2.25in; text-indent: -0.5in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Assist. Commr. &amp; Secretary for Lands &amp; Survey<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>File copy not signed.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dr. Mueller,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">&amp;c. &amp;c. &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne.</p>
         </div>
